Package: wizrd
Type: Package
Title: Integration of Large Language Models (LLMs) into R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
		person(given = "Michael", family = "Lawrence",
		       role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "michafla@gene.com")
	   )
Description: Ride the LLM hype llama with an abstraction for creating specialized
	     agents on top of various LLM backends, commercially hosted or
	     local. Craft and optimize parameterized prompts. Chat using text
	     and images. Stream chat responses. Generate embeddings and realize
	     the RAG to riches dream. Implement tools using R functions and
	     instruct the model to call them. Construct an agent by wrapping a
	     model in an R function. Use cases include generating code, guiding
	     data exploration, and creating documentation. Powered by S7.
License: MIT
